        <abstract> 
<p>Is obliged for valuable letter [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">8123</hi>] and encloses queries about the manner of gradual obliteration of ridges or furrows in old pasture lands in various parts of England.</p> 
            <p>Gives details of his experiment to test his observations of the downward flow of worm-casts.</p> 
<p>Refers to [Lyon] Playfair, [A. C.] Ramsay, and AG’s edition of [J. B.] Jukes, [<hi rend="italic">A student’s manual of geology</hi>, 3d ed., 1872].</p> 
        </abstract>
